What did you mean by offset?

My point was that your clubs appear to have little offset which is the preferred path of a low handicap ball striker. Someone who shoots what you shoot would more often times choose more forgiveness in a higher offset iron. More offset is easier to hit vs less offset which are designed for higher handicaps as more offset helps shitty golfers achieve a higher trajectory. 

It was my always intelligent, though subtly humorous way of saying you‚Äôre not a low handicap and maybe a bunch of YouTube swing tips would improve your swing to the point of being capable of hitting a low-handicap iron like the ones in the picture that appear to have little offset but there was irony in there as well in the sense that YouTube swing tips are more likely to hurt your game than help, ‚Ä¶and then there was even another layer of irony in there too bc I implied you were dumb enough to turn to YouTube for swing tips.
